  "text": "Hogwild! Asynchronous training has been studied in several other contexts, the most well-known of which is Hogwild! [CITATION_1] . In Hogwild! settings, as in pipeline-parallel settings, gradients are computed based on delayed versions of weights. However, these delays are random and can vary from step to step and weight to weight, unlike the fixed pipeline delay that we have in the pipeline-parallel setting. In Appendix E we extend and apply PipeMare to this setting [CITATION_2] showing that it can also improve final model accuracies here.",
